## 4b. Spatial UI (PanelUI) — MANDATORY for All Game UI

**CRITICAL: Do NOT use HTML DOM overlays (`<div>`, `<canvas>`, HTML elements) for
any game UI — menus, HUDs, scorecards, settings, overlays, etc. HTML overlays are
invisible in XR.** All UI must be built with IWSDK's spatial PanelUI system.

### Architecture

IWSDK's spatial UI is built on [`@pmndrs/uikit`](https://github.com/pmndrs/uikit)
and compiled via `@iwsdk/vite-plugin-uikitml`:

- **`.uikitml` files** — HTML-like markup compiled to JSON at build time
- **`PanelUI` component** — attaches compiled UI to an entity as a 3D panel
- **`ScreenSpace` component** — CSS-like positioning in browser; auto-returns to world-space in XR
- **`Follower` component** — head-locked panels that follow the player (HUDs)
- **`UIKitDocument`** — DOM-like API (`getElementById`, `querySelector`, etc.)

### Setup

Ensure `spatialUI: true` in world features (this is the default):

```typescript
const world = await World.create(container, {
  features: { spatialUI: true },
});
```

Install the uikitml vite plugin (included in generated apps):

```bash
npm install -D @iwsdk/vite-plugin-uikitml
```

Add to `vite.config.ts`:

```typescript
import { uikitml } from '@iwsdk/vite-plugin-uikitml';
// Add to plugins array alongside iwsdkDev
plugins: [uikitml(), iwsdkDev({ ai: { mode: 'agent' } })]
```

### Creating UI Panels

1. Write a `.uikitml` file in `ui/` directory:

```html
<!-- ui/hud.uikitml -->
<style>
  .hud-panel {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 2;
    background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.8);
    border-color: #00ffff;
    border-width: 0.1;
    border-radius: 1;
  }
  .score-text {
    font-size: 3;
    color: #00ffff;
    font-weight: bold;
  }
  .label {
    font-size: 1.5;
    color: #a0a0a0;
  }
</style>
<div class="hud-panel">
  <span class="label">SCORE</span>
  <span id="score-value" class="score-text">0</span>
</div>
```

2. Attach to an entity with `PanelUI`:

```typescript
import { PanelUI, ScreenSpace, Follower, FollowBehavior, PanelDocument, UIKitDocument } from '@iwsdk/core';

// World-space panel (e.g., a menu board floating in the scene)
const menuEntity = world.createTransformEntity(undefined, { persistent: true });
menuEntity.object3D.position.set(0, 1.5, -2);
menuEntity.addComponent(PanelUI, {
  config: '/ui/menu.json',   // compiled from ui/menu.uikitml
  maxWidth: 0.8,
  maxHeight: 1.0,
});

// Head-following HUD (visible in XR, follows gaze)
const hudEntity = world.createTransformEntity(undefined, { persistent: true });
hudEntity.addComponent(PanelUI, {
  config: '/ui/hud.json',
  maxWidth: 0.3,
  maxHeight: 0.15,
});
hudEntity.addComponent(Follower, {
  target: world.player.head,
  offsetPosition: [0.25, -0.15, -0.5],
  behavior: FollowBehavior.PivotY,
  speed: 5,
  tolerance: 0.3,
});

// Screen-space panel (CSS positioning in browser, world-space in XR)
const overlayEntity = world.createTransformEntity(undefined, { persistent: true });
overlayEntity.addComponent(PanelUI, {
  config: '/ui/overlay.json',
  maxWidth: 0.4,
  maxHeight: 0.3,
});
overlayEntity.addComponent(ScreenSpace, {
  width: '40vw',
  height: 'auto',
  bottom: '24px',
  right: '24px',
  zOffset: 0.25,
});
```

### Updating UI at Runtime

Access UI elements via `PanelDocument` → `UIKitDocument`:

```typescript
// In a system's update():
const doc = entity.getValue(PanelDocument, 'document') as UIKitDocument | undefined;
if (doc) {
  const scoreEl = doc.getElementById('score-value');
  if (scoreEl) {
    // UIKit components use signals for reactive updates
    scoreEl.text.value = `${currentScore}`;
  }
}
```

### UI Interaction with XR Controllers

PanelUI panels automatically receive pointer events from IWSDK's input system.
XR controller laser pointers can click buttons defined in `.uikitml`. Use
`cursor: pointer` in the style and standard event handling:

```html
<!-- ui/menu.uikitml -->
<button id="start-btn" class="menu-button" cursor="pointer">START GAME</button>
```

```typescript
const doc = entity.getValue(PanelDocument, 'document') as UIKitDocument;
const startBtn = doc?.getElementById('start-btn');
startBtn?.addEventListener('click', () => { startGame(); });
```

### Key Rules

1. **Never use HTML DOM** for game UI — no `document.createElement`, no
   `innerHTML`, no `<div>` overlays, no HTML canvas HUD
2. **All menus, HUDs, scorecards, settings, notifications** must be `.uikitml` panels
3. **Use `Follower`** for head-locked HUDs in XR (score, health, ammo, etc.)
4. **Use `ScreenSpace`** for browser-mode overlays that auto-adapt in XR
5. **Use world-space `PanelUI`** for in-scene menus, leaderboards, settings boards
6. **Test all UI in XR** before expanding features — UI must be readable and
   interactive with controller laser pointer

